    "summary": "Regeneron and Telix to co-develop and co-commercialize next-generation radiopharmaceutical therapies in a 50/50 cost and profit-sharing model Collaboration combines Regeneron’s leading antibody discovery/development platforms and oncology experience with Telix’s expertise in radiopharmaceutical development and manufacturing Telix to receive $40 million USD upfront for four initial programs with optionality to co-fund commercialization and profit-share, or earn up to an aggregate of $2.1 billion",
